  "text": "The Kafka Streams topology build chain flows as follows: (1) StreamsBuilder.build() delegates to InternalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology(), which traverses the DSL graph nodes and writes each to the InternalTopologyBuilder via writeToTopology(). (2) InternalTopologyBuilder holds nodeFactories, stateFactories, and builds the ProcessorTopology via its private build() method, which iterates nodeFactories in topological order, creating ProcessorNode/SourceNode/SinkNode instances and wiring state stores. addStateStore() registers StoreBuilder instances (wrapped via StoreBuilderWrapper) into stateFactories. (3) ProcessorTopology is a data class holding the assembled processor nodes, source/sink maps, state stores, and changelog mappings. (4) At runtime, StreamTask.completeRestoration() calls initializeTopology(), which iterates all ProcessorNodes in the topology and calls node.init() to initialize each processor with its context.",
